    "body" : "<p>To get the currently logged in user:</p>\n\n<pre><code>System.getProperty(\"user.name\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>To get the host name of the machine:</p>\n\n<pre><code>InetAddress.getLocalHost().getHostName();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>To answer the last part of your question, the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/net/InetAddress.html#getHostName%28%29\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Java API</a> says that getHostName() will return</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>the host name for this IP address, or if the operation is not allowed by the security check, the textual representation of the IP address.</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
