  "title" : "Java current machine name and logged in user?",
  "body" : "<p>Is it possible to get the name of the currently logged in user (Windows/Unix) and the hostname of the machine?</p>\n\n<p>I assume it's just a property of some static environment class.</p>\n\n<p>I've found this for the user name</p>\n\n<pre><code>com.sun.security.auth.module.NTSystem NTSystem = new\n        com.sun.security.auth.module.NTSystem();\nSystem.out.println(NTSystem.getName());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>and this for the machine name:</p>\n\n<pre><code>import java.net.InetAddress;\n...\nString computerName;\n...\ntry {\n    computerName = InetAddress.getLocalHost().getHostName();\n}\n\ncatch(Exception ex) {\n    ...\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Is the first one just for Windows?</p>\n\n<p>And what will the second one do, if you don't have a hostname set?</p>\n"
}